e]])\n*[[Chris Duhon]], former professional basketball player; assistant coach for [[Marshall Thundering Herd men's basketball|Marshall University]] \n*[[Trevon Duval]], professional basketball player<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goduke.com/ViewArticle.dbml?ATCLID=211644190&DB_OEM_ID=4200&Q_SEASON=2017|title=Trevon Duval Bio|last=|first=|date=|work=www.goduke.com|access-date=March 13, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mike Dunleavy, Jr.]], professional basketball player, [[Chicago Bulls]] in the NBA<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.basketball-reference.com/players/d/dunlemi02.html|title=Mike Dunleavy Jr|last=|first=|date=|work=www.basketball-reference.com|access-date=April 26, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Daniel Ewing]], professional basketball player, [[Maccabi Ashdod B.C.|Maccabi Ashdod]] of the [[Israeli Basketball Premier League|Israeli Premier League]]\n*[[Danny Ferry]], former [[Cleveland Cavaliers]] general manager, former professional basketball player, member of 2003 NBA Champion [[San Antonio Spurs]] (jersey retired)\n*[[Pat Garrity]] (M.B.A. 2011), former professional basketball player and investment professional\n*[[Mike Gminski]], ACC/ Raycom sports commentator (jersey retired)<ref>{{Cite news|url= https://www.basketball-reference.com/players/g/gminsmi01.html|title=Mike Gminski|last=|first=|date=|work=www.basketball-reference.com|access-date=July 19, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Harry Giles (basketball)|Harry Giles]], 20th pick of [[2017 NBA Draft]], NBA player for the [[Sacramento Kings]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.basketball-reference.com/players/g/gilesha01.html|title=Harry Giles|publisher=Basketball-Reference.Com|access-date=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Dick Groat]], former professional baseball and basketball player (jersey retired)\n*[[Lindsey Harding]], professional basketball player, [[Los Angeles Sparks]] in the [[Women's National Basketball Association|WNBA]] (jersey retired)\n*[[Rodney Hood]], NBA player for the [[Cleveland Cavaliers]]\n*[[Art Heyman]] (1963), former professional