s said to be very intelligent because she was \"going to major in physics at Duke\".\n* [[Lieutenant]] [[Kif Kroker]] of [[Futurama]] mentions in ''[[Amazon Women in the Mood]]'' that he sang in the Duke Boy's Chorus.\n* Dr. Jim Pomatter in ''[[Waitress (film)|Waitress]]''\n* Kelvin Jones in ''[[Outlaw (TV series)|Outlaw]]'' is an ambitious honor student who dreamed of going to Duke\n* Sloan Sabbith, a character played by [[Olivia Munn]] on [[HBO]]'s ''[[The Newsroom (U.S. TV series)|The Newsroom]]'', received her Ph.D. in Economics from Duke.\n*[[Nick Savrinn]], a character on ''[[Prison Break]]'', attended Duke as an undergraduate.\n*[[Nathan Scott]], a character played by [[James Lafferty]] on the television series ''[[One Tree Hill (TV series)|One Tree Hill]]'', received a scholarship to play basketball at Duke.\n*[[Sam Seaborn]], a character portrayed by [[Rob Lowe]] (whose son attends Duke in real life) on ''[[The West Wing]]'', graduated from Duke University School of Law.\n*In the pilot episode of ''[[Privileged (TV series)|Privileged]]'', billionaire Laurel Limoges hires recent Yale graduate Megan Smith to tutor her two granddaughters with the goal of getting them into Duke.\n* Stingo, the narrator of William Styron's novel ''[[Sophie's Choice (novel)|Sophie's Choice]]'', attended Duke as an undergraduate (as did Styron).\n*[[List of House characters#Stacy Warner|Stacy Warner]] lawyer and ex-girlfriend of main character [[Gregory House|Dr. House]] on the TV series ''[[House (TV series)|House]]'', played by [[Sela Ward]], hired as the hospital's lawyer during [[House (Season 2)|season 2]]\n* Charlotte York's brother Wesley on ''[[Sex and the City]]''\n* Quentin, the protagonist of the novel ''[[Paper Towns]]'' and its [[Paper Towns (film)|film adaptation]], is an incoming freshman at Duke.\n* Natalie, the protagonist of the movie ''[[Keith (film)|Keith]]'', is a high school tennis star who dreams of going to Duke.\n* [[Nathan Scott]], one of the protagonists