evision writer, ''[[Friday Night Lights (TV series)|Friday Night Lights]]''\n*[[Ken Jeong]] (B.S. 1990), comedian, physician, actor, ''[[Community (TV series)|Community]]'', ''[[Knocked Up]]'', ''[[Role Models]]'', ''[[The Hangover (film series)|The Hangover films]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/celebritology/post/ken-jeong-a-dukie-for-life/2011/05/21/AFPTIZ8G_blog.html|title=Ken Jeong: A Dukie for life|last=Chaney|first=Jen|date=May 21, 2011|publisher=The Washington Post|access-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n*Eric Kirsten (A.B. 1991), screenwriter, ''[[Midnight Sun (2018 film)|Midnight Sun]]'' \n*[[Belle Knox]], pornographic actress\n*[[Cody Ko]] (A.B. 2012), [[YouTube personalities|YouTube personality]] and [[Computer scientist|Computer Scientist]]\n*[[Martin Kratt]] (B.S. 1989), creator and star of PBS's ''[[Zoboomafoo]]''\n*[[Rossana Lacayo]] (B.S. 1979), Nicaraguan photographer and pioneer filmmaker\n*[[Alisa Lepselter]] (A.B. 1985), editor of director [[Woody Allen]]'s films since 1999\n* [[Kenny and Keith Lucas|Keith Lucas]] (attended law school), stand-up comedian, actor in [[22 Jump Street]], creator of [[Lucas Bros Moving Co|Lucas Bros. Moving Co.]], writer and producer of [[Untitled Fred Hampton project]]\n*[[Bascom Lamar Lunsford]] (J.D. 1913), folk musician\n*Russell Marcus, TV producer of ''[[Married With Children]]''; creator of ''[[Family Rules]]'', ''[[Brandy & Mr Whiskers]]'' and ''[[Corn & Peg]]''<ref>{{cite web|title=Russell Marcus|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/russell-marcus-5103a034|website=Linkedin|accessdate=November 17, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Tucker Max]] (J.D. 2001), author of the [[New York Times Best Seller List|''New York Times'' bestselling]] book ''[[I Hope They Serve Beer in Hell]]''; internet celebrity (TuckerMax.com)\n*[[Ben Mulroney]] (A.B. 1997), host of ''[[Canadian Idol]]'' and ''[[eTalk Daily]]''; son of former Canadian Prime Minister [[Brian Mulroney]]\n*[[Alexi Murdoch]], singer-songwriter\n*Stephanie (B