er]], MLB player\n\n====Basketball====\n*[[Alaa Abdelnaby]], former professional basketball player, college basketball analyst \n*[[Grayson Allen]] (2018), No. 21 pick of the [[2018 NBA Draft]], professional basketball player, [[Memphis Grizzlies]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.basketball-reference.com/players/a/allengr01.html|title=Grayson Allen|publisher=Basketball-Reference.Com|access-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Tommy Amaker]], [[Harvard Crimson men's basketball|Harvard University]] head basketball coach\n*[[Alison Bales]], former professional player (WNBA) \n*[[Marvin Bagley]], professional basketball player, No. 2 pick of the [[2018 NBA Draft]], NBA player for [[Sacramento Kings]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.basketball-reference.com/players/b/baglema01.html|title=Marvin Bagley III|publisher=Basketball-Reference.Com|access-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[RJ Barrett]], No.3 overall pick in the [[2019 NBA Draft]], NBA player for [[New York Knicks]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.basketball-reference.com/players/b/barrerj01.html|title=RJ Barrett|publisher=Basketball-Reference.Com|access-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Lexie Brown]], WNBA player for the [[Connecticut Sun]] \n*[[Marques Bolden]], professional basketball player<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goduke.com/ViewArticle.dbml?ATCLID=211021390&DB_OEM_ID=4200&Q_SEASON=2018|title=Marques Bolden bio|last=|first=|date=|work=www.goduke.com|access-date=June 23, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Shane Battier]], former professional basketball player<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.basketball-reference.com/players/b/battish01.html|title=Shane Battier|publisher=Basketball-Reference.Com|access-date=August 26, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Alana Beard]], professional basketball player, [[Los Angeles Sparks]] in the [[Women's National Basketball Association|WNBA]] (jersey retired)\n*[[Jay Bilas]] (A.B. 1986, J.D. 1992), [[ESPN]] sports commentator\n*[[Carlos Boozer]], professional basketball player, [[Los Angeles Lakers]] in the [[National Ba