 Bai Fu''\n|Judge\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"talkies\"/>\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[Eka Lagnachi Dusri Goshta]]''\n|Ghanashyam Kale\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=ekalagnachidusrigoshta>{{cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/marathi/news/%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AC%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%9C%E0%A5%80/%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B8/%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%AA%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%B2-%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BE-%E0%A4%AA%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%BE-%E0%A4%8F%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0-/23113|title='\u0938\u094d\u0935\u092a\u094d\u0928\u093f\u0932-\u092e\u0941\u0915\u094d\u0924\u093e' \u092a\u0941\u0928\u094d\u0939\u093e \u090f\u0915\u0924\u094d\u0930 !|work=24taas.com|accessdate=14 December 2015|date=3 January 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[Golmaal Hai Bhai Sab Golmaal Hai]]''\n|Sachin\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Swapnil-Joshi-plays-cupid-in-SAB-TVs-Golmaal-Hai-Bhai-Sab-Golmaal-Hai/articleshow/15164401.cms|title=Swapnil Joshi plays cupid in SAB TV's Golmaal Hai Bhai Sab Golmaal Hai|agency=TNN|work=The Times of India|date=26 July 2012|accessdate= 14 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|2014\n|''Dhabal Ek Timepass''\n| Himself\n|Host\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/television/tv-channels/regional/star-pravah-invites-viewers-to-its-dhabal\u2019-140508|title=Star Pravah invites viewers to its Dhabal|publisher=Indiantelevision.com|accessdate=26 January 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Kon Hoeel Marathi Crorepati]]''\n| Himself\n|Host\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timesofindia.com/TV/News/Marathi/Swwapnil-Joshi-to-host-Kon-Hoeel-Marathi-Crorepati/articleshow/53194933.cms|title=Swwapnil Joshi to host Kon Hoeel Marathi Crorepati \u2013 Times of India|publisher=|accessdate=16 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| \"[[Khatra Khatra Khatra]]\"\n| Himself\n| Guest/Recurring\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[No. 1 Yaari]]''\n| Himself\n| Host\n| \n|}\n===Web series===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" width=60%\n!scope=\"col\"| Year\n!scope=\"col\"| Title\n!scope=\"col\"| Platform \n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Ref.\n|-\n| 2020\n| Samantar\n| [[MX Player]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n|}\n\n==Brand endorsements==\n\n===Theatre===\n* ''Get Well Soon''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/being-at-ease/1129888/|title=Being at ease|date=June 2013|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Radio===\n*''Share it with Swwapnil'' \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{IMDb name|1738197}}\n*{{Twitter}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Joshi, Swapnil}}\n[[Category:20th-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:University of Mumbai alumni]]\n[[Category:Indian male television actors]]\n[[Category:Indian stand-up comedians]]\n[[Category:Participants in Indian reality television series]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Marathi cinema]]\n[[Category:Indian male soap opera actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name            = Swapnil Joshi\n|image           = Swapnil Joshi at the trailer launch of MPM 2.JPG\n|caption         = Joshi at the trailer launch of MPM 2\n|birth_date       = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs. No IMDb. No public records. See WP:BLPPRIVACY-->\n|birth_place      = [[ 18 October 1977 Mumbai]]\n|Birth_date       = \n|death_place      =\n|othername       =\n|nationality     = [[India]]n\n|occupation      = Actor\n|yearsactive     = 1989\u2013present\n|spouse           = {{unbulleted list|{{marriage|Aparna Joshi<br>|2005|2009|reason=divorced}}\n|{{marriage|Leena Aradhye<br>|2011}}\n}}\n|children        = 2\n|domesticpartner =\n|website         =\n}}\n\n'''Swwapnil Joshi''' is an [[India]]n film and television actor, in [[Hindi]] and [[Marathi language]]s. At nine years old, he appeared in the [[Ramanand Sagar]] show ''[[Uttar Ramayan]]''. He has done some of the most successful series in television such as [[Krishna (TV series)|Krishna]], ''[[Eka Lagnachi Dusri Goshta]]'' as well as films like ''[[Duniyadari]]'', ''[[Mumbai-Pune-Mumbai]]'' casting him as the lead actor. He has done a lot of comedy shows like ''[[Comedy Circus]]'' and ''[[Papad Pol \u2013 Shahabuddin Rathod Ki Rangeen Duniya]]'' in Hindi industry. Swwapnil owns a [[wrestling]] team named 'Vidarbhache Wagh' in [[Zee Maharashtra Kusti Dangal]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.televisionpost.com/zee-maharashtra-kusti-dangal-team-owners-squads-unveiled/|title=Zee Maharashtra Kusti Dangal team owners, squads unveiled|date=2018-10-22|work=TelevisionPost: Latest News, India\u2019s Television, Cable, DTH, TRAI|access-date=2018-11-04|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nAt the age of nine, Joshi started his acting career with [[Ramanand Sagar]]\u2019s show ''Uttar Ramayana'', where he played the role of young [[Kusha (Ramayana)|Kusha]]. In 1993, he was offered the role of young [[Krishna]] in another Ramanand Sagar's show named ''[[Krishna (TV series)|Krishna]]''. Later, Joshi took a break from acting and made a comeback as a youth actor with Sanjeev Bhattacharya's show ''Campus''. He then continued working in Hindi shows like ''[[Hudd Kar Di]]'', ''[[Dil Vil Pyar Vyar]]'', ''[[Des Mein Niklla Hoga Chand]]'', ''[[Hare Kkaanch Ki Choodiyaan]]'' to name a few. In 1997, he played the role of Inder in [[Zee TV]]\u2019s popular show ''[[Amanat (Indian TV series)|Amanat]]''. Then, he played the role of Dhruv, a parallel lead in the serial ''[[Kehta Hai Dil]]''. In 1997, he first played the supporting role of Vikram Dixit in the film ''[[Ghulam-E-Mustafa]]'', starring [[Nana Patekar]] and [[Raveena Tandon]].\n\nHe also portrayed the role of Dr. Prakash in the popular show ''[[Bhabhi (TV series)|Bhabhi]]''. He played the role of Arjun, [[Supriya Pilgaonkar]]'s youngest son in the show ''Kadvee Khatee Meethi'', which was a sequel of super-hit comedy show ''[[Tu Tu Main Main]]''. He also hosted the kid's talent show named ''[[Chota Packet Bada Dhamaka]]''. In 2008, he participated on [[Sony TV]]\u2019s show ''[[Mr. & Ms. TV]]'', which was judged by [[Madhur Bhandarkar]] and [[Sonali Bendre]]. He won the show along with actress Purvi Joshi. His first Marathi film was ''Manini'', where he played the lead role of Deepak Rajyadhakshya. In 2008, he acted in the multi-starrer film ''[[Checkmate (2008 film)|Checkmate]]''.\n\nHe played the role of Chingya in the comedy film ''[[Amhi Satpute]]''. He then played the lead character of Yash in the Marathi series ''Adhuri Ek Kahani'' opposite [[Kishori Godbole]]. He also acted in the comedy show ''Tere Gharchya Samor''. He played the role of Pratap in the shoe ''Ardhangini''. In 2010, he played the lead role of a boy from Pune in the hit, romantic film ''[[Mumbai-Pune-Mumbai]]'' opposite [[Mukta Barve]]. His chemistry with Barve in the film was compared to that of [[Shah Rukh Khan]] and [[Kajol]]. He also played the lead role of Yash Kumar in the Hindi film ''The Life Zindagi'' in 2011.\n\nJoshi then turned his attention towards comedy shows and participated in the first season of ''[[Comedy Circus]]''. He was paired with [[V.I.P. (comedian)|V.I.P]] and the duo was declared as runner's up of the show. Later, he was the contestant of various seasons of ''Comedy Circus'' like ''[[Comedy Circus|Comedy Circus-Chinchpokli To China]]'', ''[[Comedy Circus|Comedy Circus- 20-20]]'', ''[[Comedy Circus|Comedy Circus Ke Superstars]]'', ''[[Comedy Circus|Comedy Circus Ke Tansen]]'' and more. In the eighth season of the show named ''[[Comedy Circus|Comedy Circus- Maha Sangram]]'', he became victorious along with his partner VIP. Joshi also hosted the comedy show ''[[Ladies Special]]'' on Zee TV. He also played a small role in [[Sab TV]]\u2019s comedy show ''[[Sajan Re Jhoot Mat Bolo]]''. He played the role of Sameer on [[DD National]]\u2019s show ''[[Bajega Band Baaja]]'', which was followed by Sab TV's ''[[Papad Pol \u2013 Shahabuddin Rathod Ki Rangeen Duniya]]'', where he played the role of Vinaychand. In both the series, he was paired with [[Ami Trivedi]].\n\nIn 2012, he played the lead role of Sachin on Sab TV\u2019s comedy show ''[[Golmaal Hai Bhai Sab Golmaal Hai]]''. In the same year anchored the dance reality show ''Eka Peksha Ek'' that aired on Zee Marathi. In 2011, he played an episodic role of Siddhanth, a city boy who is married to a village bell, Gauri (played by Mukta Barve) in the show ''Madhu Ethe Ani Chandra Tithe''. Later, he judged the comedy reality show ''Fu Bai Fu'' and played the role of Ghanashyam Kale in the show ''[[Eka Lagnachi Dusri Goshta]]'' opposite Mukta Barve on Zee Marathi. He has also had his own Radio show named ''The Swapnil Joshi Show'' on [[Red FM 93.5]]. In 2013, he portrayed the role of Shreyas Talvalkar opposite [[Sai Tamhankar]] in ''[[Duniyadari]]''. In the same year, he was once again paired opposite Mukta Barve in the film ''Mangalashtak Once More'' where he played Satyajit Pathak.\n\nIn 2014, Joshi was seen opposite Sai Tamhankar once again in [[Sanjay Jadhav]]\u2019s film ''[[Pyaar Vali Love Story]]'', which upon the release took good opening and was a hit at the box office. In 2014, Joshi also hosted a talk show ''Dhabal-Ek Timepass'' on [[Star Pravah]]. In 2015, his first appearance was in the film ''[[Mitwaa]]'' as Shivam Sarang alongside [[Sonalee Kulkarni]] and [[Prarthana Behere]].[[Mitwaa]] opened to great response at the box office and was declared \u201csuper hit\u201d. His next release was opposite [[Amruta Khanvilkar]], ''[[Welcome Zindagi]]'' where he played Anand Prabhu. He next featured in Sanjay Jadhav's ''[[Tu Hi Re]]'' opposite Sai Tamhankar and [[Tejaswini Pandit]]. His final release of the year was [[Satish Rajwade]]'s ''[[Mumbai-Pune-Mumbai 2]]'', sequel of ''Mumbai-Pune-Mumbai'' opposite Mukta Barve where he played Gautam Pradhan. In 2016, his initial appearance was in R.Madhesh's film, ''Friends'' opposite Gauri Nalawde and alongside [[Sachit Patil]].\n\nHe later starred in a film ''[[Laal Ishq]]'' produced by [[Sanjay Leela Bhansali]] and directed by [[Swapna Waghmare Joshi]]. It also stars [[Anjana Sukhani]] for first time in Marathi films. It released on 27 May. He is also starring in a film [[Fugay]] along with [[Subodh Bhave]] and directed by [[Swapna Waghmare Joshi]]. He has done a family film ''[[Fugay]]'' with his brother [[Subodh Bhave]]. A change in it is that they have exchanged their surnames Subodh Joshi and Swapnil Bhave. He is also starred in the Marathi film ''[[Bhikari]]'' directed by [[Ganesh Acharya]].\n\n==Filmography==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year \n!Title \n! Role  \n!class=\"unsortable\"| Ref(s)\n|- \n| 1997 \n| ''[[Ghulam-E-Mustafa]]'' \n| Vikram Dixit \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=talkies>{{cite web|url=http://www.zeetalkies.com/celebrities/swapnil-joshi.html|title=Swapnil Joshi|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref> \n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Dil Vil Pyar Vyar]]'' \n| Anil \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"talkies\"/> \n|-\n| 2003 \n| ''Manini'' \n| Deepak Rajyadhakshya \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"talkies\"/> \n|-\n| 2008 \n| ''[[Checkmate (2008 film)|Checkmate]]'' \n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"talkies\"/> \n|-\n| 2008 \n| ''Target'' \n| Swapnil \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"talkies\"/> \n|-\n| 2009 \n| ''[[Amhi Satpute]]'' \n| Chingalya \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rediff.com/movies/review/aamhi/20080418.htm|title=Marathi Satte Pe Satta disappoints|date=18 April 2008|website= [[Rediff.com]]|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2010 \n|''[[Mumbai-Pune-Mumbai]]'' \n| Pune\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=talkies/>\n|-\n|2011\n|''The Life Zindagi''\n|Yash 'Nadan' K. Kumar\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=talkies/> \n|-\n| 2013 \n|'' [[Duniyadari]]'' \n| Shreyas Talvalkar \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/blogs/post-review-marathi-film-duniyadari-is-worth-a-watch-1862998|title=Review: Marathi film Duniyadari is worth a watch|date=20 July 2013|work=DNA|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2013 \n| Govinda\n| Rajan Mayekar \n|\n|-\n| 2013 \n|''[[Mangalashtak Once More]]'' \n| Satyajit \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi/movies/news/The-music-is-the-USP-of-Mangalashtak-Once-More/articleshow/23606850.cms|title=The music is the USP of 'Mangalashtak Once More'|work=The Times of India|agency=TNN|author=Pooja Kulkarni|date=7 November 2013 |accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2014 \n|''Por Bazaar''\n| Special Appearance \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n| 2014 \n|''[[Pyaar Vali Love Story]]'' \n| Amar \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/screen/pyaar-vali-love-story-on-october-2/|title=Pyaar Vali Love Story on October 2|date=11 April 2014|work=The Indian Express|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015 \n| ''[[Mitwaa]]'' \n| Shivam Sarang \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi/movies/news/Swapnils-aversion-to-six-packs/articleshow/46200389.cms|title=Swapnil's aversion to six-packs|work=The Times of India|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|2015\n|''2 Premi Premache''\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|last1=Joshi|first1=Swapnil|title=Swwapnil to play tumour patient|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi/movies/news/Swwapnil-to-play-tumour-patient/articleshow/47368443.cms|accessdate=25 May 2015|agency=Times of India|issue=21 May 2015|publisher=Times of India|date=21 May 2015|ref=2 Premi Premache}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015 \n| ''[[Welcome Zindagi]]'' \n| Anand Prabhu\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.punemirror.in/entertainment/marathi-reviews/Film-Reviews-No-thank-you/articleshow/47835259.cms|title=Film Reviews: No, thank you|work=[[Mumbai Mirror|Pune Mirror]]|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015 \n| ''[[Tu Hi Re]]'' \n| Siddharth\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=http://m.timesofindia.com/tv/news/hindi/Swwapnil-Sai-and-Tejaswini-talk-about-friendship-and-love-post-marriage/articleshow/48791121.cms|title=Swwapnil Sai and Tejaswini talk about friendship and love post marriage|date=3 September 2015|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015 \n| ''[[Mumbai-Pune-Mumbai 2]]'' \n| Gautam Pradhan\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.co.in/a-film-should-have-the-ability-to-spread-happiness/|title=A film should have the ability to spread happiness|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|''Friends''\n|Neil\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.loksatta.com/manoranjan-news/freinds-movie-releasing-on-15th-january-1186859/|title=\u0938\u094d\u0935\u092a\u094d\u0928\u0940\u0932-\u0938\u091a\u093f\u0924\u091a\u0940 '\u092b\u094d\u0930\u0947\u0923\u094d\u0921\u0936\u0940\u092a'|date=8 January 2016|work=Loksatta|accessdate=26 January 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Laal Ishq (film)|Laal Ishq]]''\n|Yash Patwardhan\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Fugay]]''\n|Aditya\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Bhikari]]''\n|Samrat Jaikar\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''Ranangan''\n|\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Mumbai Pune Mumbai 3]]''\n|Gautam Pradhan\n|\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Mogra Phulaalaa]]''\n|Sunil Kulkarni \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite tweet|user=taran_adarsh| author=Tara