{"title_page": "1972 World Cup (men's golf)", "text_new": "{{use mdy dates|date = January 2020}}\n{{Infobox individual golf tournament\n| name          = 1972 World Cup\n| image         = \n| caption       = \n| dates         = 9\u201312 November\n| location      = [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]]\n| coordinates   = \n| course        = [[Royal Melbourne Golf Club]]<br>(Composite of East and West Courses)\n| lang          = <!-- Defaults to US English. Value must be \"uk\" for British English -->\n| org           = \n| tour          = \n| format        = 54 holes [[stroke play]]<br>combined score\n| par           = 71\n| yardage       = {{convert|6,944|yd|m}}\n| field         = 43 two-man teams\n| cut           = None\n| purse         = US$6,300\n| winners_share = $2,000 team<br>$1,000 individual\n| champion      = {{ROC}}<br>[[Hsieh Min-Nan]] & [[Lu Liang-huan]]\n| score         = 438 (+12)\n| map           = \n| map_label     = \n| map_caption   = \n| map_relief =\n| map_label_position =\n| map_size =\n| previous      = [[1971 World Cup (men's golf)|1971]]\n| next          = [[1973 World Cup (men's golf)|1973]]\n}}\nThe '''1972 World Cup''' took place 9\u201312 November at [[Royal Melbourne Golf Club]] in [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]]. It was the 20th [[World Cup (men's golf)|World Cup]] event. The tournament was a [[stroke play]] team event, shortened from 72 holes, after the second round, scheduled on Friday, was cancelled due to bad weather, to 54 holes with 43 teams. Each team consisted of two players from a country. The combined score of each team determined the team results. The [[Republic of China]] team of [[Hsieh Min-Nan]] and [[Lu Liang-huan]] won by two strokes over the [[Japan]] team of [[Takaaki Kono]] and [[Takashi Murakami (golfer)|Takashi Murakami]]. The individual competition was won by Hsieh two strokes ahead of Kono. This was the first team victory for the Republic of China, also known as Taiwan, in the history of the World Cup, founded in 1953 and until 1967 named the Canada Cup.\n\n== Teams ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!Country\n!Players\n|-\n|{{ARG}}\n|[[Roberto De Vicenzo]] and [[Vicente Fern\u00e1ndez (golfer)|Vicente Fern\u00e1ndez]]\n|-\n|{{AUS}}\n|[[Bruce Crampton]] and [[Bill Dunk]]\n|-\n|{{AUT}}\n|[[Oswald Gartenmaier]] and [[Rudolf Hauser (golfer)|Rudolf Hauser]]\n|-\n|{{BEL}}\n|[[Donald Swaelens]] and [[Flory Van Donck]]\n|-\n|{{BRA}}\n|[[Jose Maria Gonzalez Jr]] and [[Luis Carlos Pinto]]\n|-\n|{{CAN}}\n|[[Phil Giroux]] and [[Bob Panasik]]\n|-\n|{{CHL}}\n|[[Francisco Cerda]] and [[Rafael Jerez]]\n|-\n|{{COL}}\n|[[Alfonso Boh\u00f3rquez]] and [[Juan Pinzon]]\n|-\n|{{DNK}}\n|[[Herluf Hansen]] and [[Henning Kristensen]]\n|-\n|{{EGY}}\n|[[Farouk Badr]] and [[Mohamed Said Moussa]]\n|-\n|{{ENG}}\n|[[Guy Hunt (golfer)|Guy Hunt]] and [[Tony Jacklin]]\n|-\n|{{FRA}}\n|[[Jean Gara\u00efalde]] and [[Bernard Pascassio]]\n|-\n|{{GRC}}\n|[[John Sotiropoulos]] and [[George Vafiadis]] (a)\n|-\n|{{HKG}}\n|[[Joseph Hardwick]] and [[Peter Tang]]\n|-\n|{{IDN}}\n|[[Salim Denim]] and Soeparno\n|-\n|{{IRL}}\n|[[Jimmy Kinsella]] and [[John O'Leary (golfer)|John O'Leary]]\n|-\n|{{ITA}}\n|[[Roberto Bernardini]] and [[Alberto Croce]]\n|-\n|{{JAM}}\n|[[Peter Millhouse]] and [[Seymore Rose]]\n|-\n|{{flagcountry|JPN|1947}}\n|[[Takaaki Kono]] and [[Takashi Murakami (golfer)|Takashi Murakami]]\n|-\n|{{LBY}}\n|[[Mohammed Salah Ziaani]] and [[Muftah Salem]]\n|-\n|{{MYS}}\n|[[Zainal Abidin (golfer)|Zainal Abidin]] and [[Bobby Lim|Bobby Lim Yat Foong]]\n|-\n|{{flagcountry|MEX|1934}}\n|[[Ram\u00f3n Cruz]] and [[Victor Regalado]]\n|-\n|{{MAR}}\n|[[Omar Ben El-Harcha]] and [[Benrokia Massaoud]]\n|-\n|{{NLD}}\n|[[Jan Dorrestein]] and [[Bertus Van Mook]]\n|-\n|{{NZL}}\n|[[Bob Charles (golfer)|Bob Charles]] and [[Walter Godfrey (golfer)|Walter Godfrey]]\n|-\n|{{NGA}}\n|[[Patrick Okpomu]] and [[Paul Osanebi]]\n|-\n|{{PER}}\n|[[Bernabe Fajaro]] and [[Raul Travieso]]\n|-\n|{{flagcountry|PHL|1936}}\n|[[Ben Arda]] and [[Ireneo Legaspi]]\n|-\n|{{PRT}}\n|[[Henrique Paulino]] and [[Joaquin Rodrigues]]\n|-\n|{{flagcountry|PRI|1952}}\n|[[David Jimenez (golfer)|David Jimenez]] and [[Dan Murphy (golfer)|Dan Murphy]]\n|-\n|{{ROC}}\n|[[Lu Liang-Huan]] and [[Hsieh Min-Nan]]\n|-\n|{{ROU}}\n|[[Dumitru Muneanu]] (a) and [[Paul Tomita]]\n|-\n|{{SCO}}\n|[[Harry Bannerman]] and [[Ronnie Shade]]\n|-\n|{{SGP}}\n|David Milne and [[Phua Thin Kiay]] \n|-\n|{{flagcountry|ZAF|1928}}\n|[[Tienie Britz]] and [[Gary Player]]\n|-\n|{{flagcountry|KOR|1949}}\n|[[Hahn Sang-chan]] and [[Kim Seung-hack]]\n|-\n|{{flagcountry|ESP|1945}}\n|[[Valent\u00edn Barrios]] and [[\u00c1ngel Gallardo (golfer)|\u00c1ngel Gallardo]]\n|-\n|{{SWE}}\n|[[Eric Ericsson (golfer)|Eric Ericsson]] and [[Jonas Peil]]\n|-\n|{{CHE}}\n|[[Bernard Cordonier]] and [[Ronald Tingley]]\n|-\n|{{THA}}\n|[[Sukree Onsham]] and [[Long Toyai]]\n|-\n|{{USA}}\n|[[Jim Jamieson]] and [[Tom Weiskopf]]\n|-\n|{{WAL}}\n|[[Kim Dabson]] and [[David Vaughan (golfer)|David Vaughan]]\n|-\n|{{FRG}}\n|[[Roman Krause]] and [[Gerhard K\u00f6nig]]\n|}\n(a) denotes amateur\n\nSources:<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.newspapers.com/newspage/121932770/ |title=Players and their countries |newspaper=The Age |location=Melbourne, Victoria, Australia |date=November 8, 1972 |page=5 (Golf Special) |via=newspapers.com |url-access=subscription}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/121932545 |title=Cup layers & countries (continued) |newspaper=The Age |location=Melbourne, Victoria, Australia |date=November 8, 1972 |page=7 (Golf Special) |via=newspapers.com |url-access=subscription}}</ref>\n\n== Scores ==\n'''Team'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!#\n!Country\n!Score\n!To par\n!Money (US$)<br>(per team)\n|-\n|align=center|1 || {{ROC}} || 144-141-153=438 || align=center|+12 || align=center|2,000\n|-\n|align=center|2 || {{flagcountry|JPN|1947}} || 141-145-154=440 || align=center|+14 || align=center|1,000\n|-\n|align=center|3 || {{flagcountry|ZAF